==English==

===Etymology===
''[[ape|Ape]]''+''[[shit]]'', possibly from the tendency of certain primate species to throw faeces when extremely annoyed.

===Adjective===
'''apeshit'''

# {{slang}} Out of control from anger or excitement.  Often used with ''go''.
#: ''I told him the bad news, and he went apeshit.''
#: ''I told him the bad news, and now he's totally apeshit.''
# {{slang, less common}} [[awesome|Awesome]].
#:''This dope is apeshit.''

===Noun===
'''apeshit'''

# {{slang}} A [[murderous]] [[rampage]].
#: ''Turn on CNN, there's an apeshit in progress.''
